                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The soul glutton casts mind reading on a dying creature (or the corpse of a creature that died no more than 24 hours ago). If a dying creature fails its save, it must immediately attempt a recovery check. If the creature dies as a result of this check (or if the target was a fresh corpse), the soul glutton consumes a significant portion of the creature's soul and restores @Damage[30[healing]] Hit Points, gaining any Hit Points in excess of its maximum as temporary Hit Points that last for 24 hours. A creature slain in this way can be returned to life normally once the soul glutton that killed it has been slain, otherwise any attempt to restore life requires a @Check[flat|dc:15] for success.</p>"
                },
